Terms and Conditions of Service Use

Before using the services of the Fast Changer service, the User must fully familiarize themselves with the Rules and Conditions for providing services by the Fast Changer service. Using the services of the Fast Changer service is only possible if the User accepts all the terms of the agreement. Rules and conditions for providing services by the Fast Changer service.

Terms and Definitions

1.1. Fast Changer ("Service") – a service providing digital currency exchange services.

1.2. User – any individual who agrees with all the conditions offered by the Service and joins this agreement. The User and the Service are collectively referred to as the "Parties."

1.3. Request – information submitted by the User using the Service’s tools electronically, reflecting their intent to use the Service’s services under the terms offered by the Service and specified in the request parameters.

1.4. Exchange – operations involving the transfer of digital currency from one holder to another using funds.

1.5. Exchange Rate – the cost ratio of two exchanged currencies.

1.6. Agreement – the contract entered into between the Parties for the exchange of digital currencies based on the rules and conditions set by the Service.

Subject of the Agreement and Procedure for Its Entry into Force

2.1. The subject of this agreement is the services related to the exchange of digital currencies, provided by the Service upon the User’s request, as well as other services described on the Service’s website.

2.2. The Agreement is considered accepted upon the submission of a Request by the User, which is an integral part of this Agreement. Each User's request constitutes a new Agreement under the terms in effect at the time of submission.

2.3. This Agreement comes into effect upon the completion of the Request by the User and the assignment of a unique request number.

2.4. The date, time, and parameters of the Request are automatically fixed by the Service when the Request is completed and a unique request number is assigned.

2.5. This Agreement ceases to be valid once the User sends the required funds or digital currency as per the Request parameters or if the request is canceled.

2.6. The Service reserves the right to unilaterally make changes to this Agreement without notifying the User, but with the mandatory publication of the updated version of the Agreement on this page.

Conditions for Providing Services

3.1. Only Users who have fully familiarized themselves with and agree to the terms and conditions set by the Fast Changer service may use the services of the Service.

3.2. The Service automatically sets the exchange rate and publishes it on the Service’s website.

3.3. The Service has the right to change the exchange rates at any time unilaterally, notifying Users by publishing the updated information on the Service's website.

3.4. Exchange rate fixation and changes during the request:

• The rate is fixed for 10 minutes from the moment of exchange direction selection. After this time, a new rate will be offered.

• If the User completes the Request within 10 minutes, the rate is extended for 15 more minutes to allow payment. If the User doesn’t make the payment and change the status to "Paid" within this time, a new exchange rate will be offered.

• The Service reserves the right to change the exchange rate if more than 8 hours have passed since the transaction appeared on the digital currency network and there are fewer than 2 confirmations from the network.

• The Service reserves the right to change the exchange rate if there is an error in the request due to the User’s fault and the User hasn’t provided correct information within 8 hours.

• The Service reserves the right to change the exchange rate if the original rate changes by more than 1% before payment and the request status is not updated to "Paid".

3.5. The User manages the exchange process or obtains information about the status of the service via the relevant user interface located on the Service’s website.

3.5.1. Tron exchanges work via a payment gateway on a smart contract. A fee of 1 TRX is charged during transfers. Whole numbers from 2000 (3000, 4000, 5000, and so on) are accepted. If a non-whole number is received (e.g., 2999), the transaction will be frozen by the smart contract until the missing amount is received. To complete the transaction, the user needs to top up the same wallet starting from 2000 TRX.

3.6. The Service conducts exchanges for the User’s requests in strict accordance with its privacy policy and anti-money laundering and anti-illegal transaction policies.

3.7. Any completed operation performed by the Service according to the User's request cannot be canceled by the User after the funds or digital currencies have been sent by the Service to the User.

3.8. If the User does not send the funds or digital currency within one hour after creating the request, the Agreement is considered terminated unilaterally by the Service as not having been enacted.

3.9. In case of termination of the agreement, any funds or digital currencies received after the specified period may be refunded to the User’s provided account details upon request. The User is responsible for any commission fees for the refund.

3.10. If the amount of funds or digital currencies received differs from the amount specified by the User, the Service may unilaterally terminate the agreement and return the received funds to the User’s account or recalculate the amount based on the fixed exchange rate. The User is responsible for any commission fees related to the refund.

Privacy Policy

4.1. The Service accepts the User's personal data for transactions, which the Service agrees to store in an encrypted form, not disclose, and not transfer to third parties, except in cases described in p. 4.4 and p. 5.5 of this Agreement.

4.2. All transactions and personal data transmissions between the User and the Service are conducted through an encrypted SSL channel with a 256-bit key.

4.3. The Service has the right to collect additional data about the User using any available methods if necessary. The collected information will not be disclosed or transferred to third parties except as provided in p. 4.4 and p. 5.5.

4.4. The Service has the right to transfer personal data of the User and details of their transactions to law enforcement or court authorities upon official request or to protect its own rights.

4.5. All data collected about the User and transaction details are stored in the Service’s database for five years.

Anti-Money Laundering and Illegal Activity Policy

5.1. In accordance with international law, the Service implements various rules and procedures aimed at preventing the use of the Service for money laundering or illegal activities.

5.2. To prevent illegal activities, the Service sets specific requirements for all Requests made by the User:

• Transfers to third parties are strictly prohibited.

• All contact details entered by the User must be accurate and true.

• The use of anonymous proxies or connections to the internet is strictly prohibited when making Requests.

5.3. The Service reserves the right to suspend all current requests from the User until copies of identification documents and other necessary information are provided to verify the transaction in certain cases, such as suspicion of illegal activity.

5.4. If the User refuses to provide the requested documents, the Service reserves the right to refuse further service and take actions described in p. 3.14.

5.5. The Service reserves the right to refuse further service to the User and take actions described in p. 3.14, and may transfer all collected data to law enforcement authorities in the following cases:

• Transactions aimed at money laundering, terrorism financing, fraud, or any other illegal activities.

• The suspicion that the User’s identification document is counterfeit or invalid.

• Receipt of information indicating that the User does not have legal ownership of the funds or digital currencies.

Limitation of Liability

6.1. The User guarantees that they are not a citizen or tax resident of the United States, North Korea, or Iran.

6.2. Only individuals who have reached the age of majority can use the Service.

6.3. The User agrees that the Service’s liability is limited to the funds received from the User to fulfill the agreement’s subject, and the Service does not provide additional guarantees or assume additional liability.

6.4. The Service will make every effort but does not guarantee that its services will be available 24/7. The Service is not responsible for any losses, missed profits, or other costs incurred by the User due to the inability to access the website or services.

6.5. The Service is not liable for losses, missed profits, or any other costs incurred by the User due to delays, errors, or failures in banking payments or electronic transfers.

General Provisions

1.1. This document defines the policy of the EXMO.LIFE website (hereinafter referred to as the Operator) regarding the processing of personal data of website users and outlines the system of key principles applied in relation to personal data processing.

1.2. The policy regarding the processing of personal data of website users (hereinafter referred to as the Policy) is developed to comply with the requirements of the legislation of the Russian Federation, which includes personal data and identification of users visiting the site. The Policy applies to all personal data that is processed by the Operator.

1.3. The Policy is developed in accordance with the Constitution of the Russian Federation, the Civil Code of the Russian Federation, the Federal Law No. 152-FZ "On Personal Data" dated July 27, 2006, and other applicable legislation of the Russian Federation in the field of personal data protection.

1.4. The Policy establishes the procedure for processing personal data of website users: actions for collecting, systematizing, accumulating, storing, clarifying (updating, modifying), and destroying personal data.

1.5. The Policy establishes mandatory requirements and rules for the employees of the Operator involved in servicing the website, regarding all types of information carriers containing personal data of website users.

1.6. The Policy does not address issues regarding the security of personal data classified as state secrets by Russian Federation law.

1.7. Terms and Definitions:

Personal data – any information directly or indirectly related to a specific or identifiable individual (subject of personal data).

Operator – a government agency, municipal authority, legal entity, or individual who organizes and/or performs personal data processing, as well as determines the purposes, scope, and actions to be performed with personal data.

Personal data processing – any action (operation) or set of actions (operations) performed with personal data, either with or without the use of automated tools, including collection, recording, systematization, accumulation, storage, clarification (updating, modification), extraction, use, transfer (distribution, provision, access), anonymization, blocking, deletion, destruction.

User – an Internet user.

Automated personal data processing – processing of personal data using computing technology.

Provision of personal data – actions aimed at disclosing personal data to a particular person or group of individuals.

Blocking of personal data – temporary cessation of personal data processing (except where processing is required to clarify personal data).

Destruction of personal data – actions that make it impossible to restore the content of personal data in the personal data information system and/or result in the destruction of material carriers of personal data.

Anonymization of personal data – actions that make it impossible to determine the affiliation of personal data to a specific subject of personal data without using additional information.

1.8. The Operator ensures the confidentiality and security of personal data during processing in accordance with legal requirements and does not disclose or distribute personal data to third parties without the consent of the subject of personal data unless otherwise provided by federal law. In accordance with the list of personal data processed on the website, the personal data of website users are considered confidential information.

2. Main Rights and Obligations of the Operator and the Subject of Personal Data

2.1. The Operator has the right to:

Receive personal data from personal data subjects and third parties (persons not being subjects of personal data), with the Operator fulfilling the obligations set out in the Federal Law No. 152-FZ "On Personal Data."

Independently determine the composition and list of measures necessary and sufficient to ensure compliance with the obligations established by the Law on Personal Data and related regulations, unless otherwise provided by the Law on Personal Data or other federal laws.

In case of withdrawal of consent for personal data processing by the subject, the Operator may continue processing personal data without consent if there are grounds specified in the Law on Personal Data.

2.2. The Operator is obligated to:

Organize personal data processing in compliance with the requirements of the Law on Personal Data.

Respond to requests and inquiries from personal data subjects and their legal representatives as required by the Law on Personal Data.

2.3. The Subject of Personal Data has the right to:

Receive information concerning the processing of their personal data, except in cases specified by federal laws. The information must be provided by the Operator in an accessible form and should not contain personal data related to other subjects of personal data unless there are legal grounds for disclosure of such data.

Request clarification, blocking, or destruction of their personal data if the data is incomplete, outdated, inaccurate, unlawfully obtained, or unnecessary for the stated purpose of processing.

Other rights as provided in Chapter 3 of the Federal Law No. 152-FZ "On Personal Data" dated July 27, 2006.

3. Purposes of Personal Data Collection

3.1. Personal data processing is limited to achieving specific, pre-determined, and legitimate purposes. Processing of personal data incompatible with the purposes of collection is prohibited.

3.2. Only personal data that is necessary for the stated purposes of processing will be processed.

3.3. The processing of personal data of website users is conducted solely for the purpose of enabling user interaction with the website.

3.4. The personal data on the website consists of any information related to a specific or identifiable individual (subject of personal data).

4. Scope of Processed Personal Data

4.1. The content and scope of processed personal data of website users align with the stated purposes of processing, as outlined in Section 3 of this Policy. Processed personal data should not be excessive in relation to the declared processing purposes.

4.2. The Operator may process the following personal data of users:

Source of website access (websites) and information from search or advertising queries.

Data about the user's device (including resolution, version, and other attributes).

User clicks, page views, form fillings, banner and video views.

Data about audience segments.

Session parameters.

Data about the time of visit.

User identifier stored in cookies.

Last name, first name, patronymic.

Contact phone number.

Email address.

4.3. The Operator does not process special categories of personal data related to race, ethnicity, political views, religious or philosophical beliefs, health status, or intimate life, except in cases provided by Russian Federation legislation.

4.4. The Operator does not process biometric personal data.

4.5. The Operator does not engage in cross-border transfer of personal data.

5. Procedure and Conditions for Personal Data Processing

5.1. Personal data processing is carried out by the Operator in accordance with the requirements of Russian Federation legislation.

5.2. Personal data processing is carried out with the consent of the subjects of personal data, as well as without it in cases provided by Russian Federation legislation.

5.3. The Operator conducts both automated and non-automated personal data processing.

5.4. Only employees of the Operator whose duties involve personal data processing are allowed to handle personal data.

5.5. The disclosure, provision, or distribution of personal data to third parties is prohibited without the consent of the subject, unless otherwise stipulated by federal law.

5.6. The transfer of personal data to investigative bodies, the Federal Tax Service, the Pension Fund of the Russian Federation, the Social Insurance Fund, and other authorized bodies is conducted in accordance with Russian Federation legislation.

5.7. The Operator takes necessary legal, organizational, and technical measures to protect personal data from unauthorized access, destruction, modification, blocking, distribution, and other unlawful actions, including:

Identifying security threats during personal data processing.

Implementing local regulations governing personal data processing and protection.

Creating necessary conditions for working with personal data.

Organizing document accounting containing personal data.

Organizing work with information systems processing personal data.

Storing personal data in conditions ensuring their preservation and preventing unauthorized access.

5.8. The Operator stores personal data in a form that allows identifying the subject of personal data for no longer than necessary for the purposes of data processing unless the retention period is stipulated by federal law or contract.

5.9. When collecting personal data, including via the Internet, the Operator ensures the recording, systematization, accumulation, storage, clarification (updating, modification), and extraction of personal data of Russian Federation citizens using databases located within the territory of the Russian Federation, except in cases provided by the Law on Personal Data.
